hopobject.body: What do you do for a living? imiquimod rxlist Tourism business is already being damaged by rumors that certain travel services will halt as non-essential government services close during a government shutdown, says Patricia Rojas-Ungar, vice president government relations for the U.S. Travel Association. Rojas-Ungar says her group has instructed its trade association members, including hotels, car rental companies, airports and state tourism offices, to tell their members of Congress about tourism business they are losing and to ask them to negotiate on a deal that would end the shutdown.
